Dynamo Kiev , Celtic and CFR Cluj won
on the road to hold the advantage in their Champions League
playoff ties.  Kiev recovered after losing an early goal to win 3-1 at
Borussia Monchengladbach, Celtic defeated Helsingborgs 2-0 and
Cluj rallied with two goals in five minutes from Modou Sougou to
win 2-1 at Basel.  Also tonight,  Spartak Moscow  won 2-1 against the visiting
Fenerbahce and Copenhagen took a 1-0 lead in its tie against
Lille, which will host the second leg.  The winners of the two-game series advance to the group
phase of European soccerâ€™s elite tournament. The return games
will be played Aug. 29.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
